Results Template

A Subtitle

Introduction

This is a template for a data analysis folder that can be easily exported as a webpage or as Supplementary Materials (e.g., as a word document). The README page of the repository, alongside the webpage and word document, were all created from this single index.Rmd that you can edit.

  • How to use this template?

Download it (click here to download), unzip it and edit.

  • How to upload it to a website?

Upload the whole folder to GitHub, go to settings and enable GitHub pages, and select the docs/ folder as the location of the webpage. Indeed, rendering (knitting) the files will generate an index.html file in the /docs/ folder, which is used as the website. You can see an example at https://realitybending.github.io/ResultsTemplate/.

  • How to add references?

References have to be added in bib format in the utils/bibliography.bib file, and further referenced in the text like this (Ldecke, Waggoner, & Makowski, 2019).
